<sec>
<st>
Career</st>
<p>

Harper broke into both film and television in 1993, doing recurring work on the Fox series <it><link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../943/18943.xml">
Married...with Children</link></it> and making his film debut in the short <it>Confessions of a Dog</it>. He had his first substantial role in a feature in <actor wordnetid="109765278" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../941/26941.xml">
Spike Lee</link></actor>
's <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../345/4770345.xml">
Get on the Bus</link></movie>
</it> (1996), which cast him as a UCLA film student riding a bus to the Million Man March in Washington, D.C. He went on to further demonstrate his versatility in such films as Lee's <it><movie wordnetid="106613686" confidence="0.9508927676800064">
<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../364/1644364.xml">
He Got Game</link></movie>
</it> (1998) and <physical_entity wordnetid="100001930" confidence="0.8">
